      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-06-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2022-01-10T14:31:49Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>COVID-19 Origins Accountability Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the President to impose sanctions and take other actions related to COVID-19 if certain conditions are not met.</p> <p>Specifically, if the President is unable to certify within 90 days of this bill's enactment that China's government has allowed a transparent international forensic investigation into the origins of COVID-19 and certain laboratories in the city of Wuhan, the President must (1) impose visa- and property-blocking sanctions against individuals employed by or affiliated with the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), (2) prohibit federal funding for collaborative projects between U.S.-based researchers and CAS researchers in any academic field, and (3) prohibit U.S.-based researchers and institutions that receive federal funding from engaging in certain research on viruses with individuals or institutions based in China.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
